	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Re: Discuss Class Re-Envisionment

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bdruidbalancem3515_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('3515');showLiMenu(this,'io_bdruidbalancem3515','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('3515');showLiMenu(this,'io_bdruidbalancem3515','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=91297'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>Maelin-Faedok</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 32<br>
				
				Registered: 02-14-2005
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=91297'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/paladin.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3515#M3515">51</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 785 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I don't play a druid. I sit next to one though when I play...<br><br>I've played now every EQ game that's multiplayer - EQ, EQOA, and EQ2.<br><br>While the proposed changes are a start, and are something... can any dev answer me this one?<br><br>EQOA - Druids and Shamans have resurrect spells, along with Clerics.<br>EQ2 - Priests have revive/resurrect spells (later on becoming Druids and Shamans)<br>EQ - Where did the spells go?<br><br>Clerics will undoubtably whine about druids and shamans getting anything that resembles a class attribute, but honestly until a Druid can wear full sets of plate and get the exact same heal and stun spells as a cleric, it's all childish complaints.<br><br>If you want to make Druids (and Shamans) more appealing to groups, or a more acceptable as a replacement for a cleric, then you're going to have to give Druids and Shamans a few things that Clerics get. It's unavoidable.<br><br>The idea of the Shape Change is a nice one. It'd be more roleplayed -- lets say a wolf form for offense, and a treant form for defense. Tack on spell haste for the specific spells, and a mana reduction, and you've got Druids who can keep up.<br><br>After hearing my girlfriend's complaints, the biggest issue I've heard is that she's just not powerful enough. We're both playing toons in the mid-50's (She's 57, me a 56 Pal) and she can't find a use for her characater when we've got clerics, wizards, and necros everywhere. You have to think at our level - AAs aren't much of an option. It's smarter to wait until 60, which we're doing. We've just got enough AA's for Run 3 (which is always good) and what ever AAs come from various PoP progression quests. So all she has are her raw spells. She has focus items here and there, and her gear is pretty darn good. So where's the fault? Why does it take her entire mana bar to kill one turtle in Natimbi?<br><br>I remember the days when people cried for nerfs for Druids. I remember the days when a Druid could solo things that even a good group couldn't kill. Why not look back at the past changes that have been made to the class and consider reversing any? I don't know any for sure, but obviously something was done somewhere along the line to turn a once powerful class into a class lacking.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-15-2005</span> <span class=time_text>03:32 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
