<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3519#M3519">55</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 773 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Alright first of all thank you Sony for considering us for something cool please see it through and don't ruin it.<br><br>Second, thank you for the clerics who have posted something comstructive here and the other classes too.<br><br><br>Now to the realy point.<br>First of all Sony doesn't seem to realize how huge an effect the -50% mod is and how little the +25% mod is. The +25% mod will not make us as good as the main classes for whatever and the -50% mod will render that side of us totally ineffective while we use it. My current 1550 DD with focus hits for max 2000ish. A 1000 DD WITH focus is TOTALLY useless. Sure I'm still using the PoP nuke but you get the idea. Ok so the 2k nuke say 2600 2700 with focus. Yay I'm gonna get a 1350 nuke one OOW + Mobs? I don't think so, it's not worth the time to cast it for the mana it's going to take. Exaggerating a bit I am but it's to stress a good point.<br><br>Perhaps a +25% bonus to effectivity of spells, -25% on cast time and mana, as well as only reducing the opposite by 35% and in effectivity only. That would be fair in this aspect. Also when you enter healing stance have our hp and ac go up. This would be in line with the supperior gear that clerics recieve. In offensive mode have our hp and ac go down. This would truely fit the spirit of a different "form."<br><br>Secondly this has come up lots but it needs to be reiterated. We NEED group heals. We are OFTEN in a tight situation where the entire group is down to about half health. It is NOT efficient to go around healing each member and if you are in a tight spot it will NOT save you. You need to concentrate on the tank first of all so if anything decides to chow on another member at this point he/she is dead. Second if you go healing one by one about half will die since we take so long to heal. Plus this is in NON-ae situations. In those situations you have no hope at all. As far as HOTs I don't care so much, clerics can keep those for all I care, but give me a 1k group heal, cast time 2-3 seconds NO MORE.<br><br>Now cut down on our cast time for heals period. Even in normal mode, we desperately heal this. There is nothing more pathetic than not being able to heal a tank in MPG just because his hp is going down faster than you can mash your best fast heal WHILE you have just cast spirit of the grove to keep him up at the same time. Yes this is not a great tank granted, but a cleric could save him in a heartbeat and frankly this game was supposed to be for people of all levels or dedication and often this is the only tank you can get.<br><br>Third I would LOVE to see a pet. A real pet. Sure sure we weren't meant to be a pet class whatever. It goes along with our class lore thing, hey nature is supposed to love us but shamen get the wolf? We all know that we are not going to get the DD output mages and wizards have so this would help even it out. Make it an AA and only available in offensive form. That would "balance" the equation because it will be well earned and limited enough.<br><br>Lastly I would like to see some form specific abilities. Like the pet I mentioned above give us some dual AAs. The last expansion didn't have any AAs for anyone and frankly the expansion before it did not give druids very inventive AAs at all. Above what everyone recieved, druids just recieved bigger versions of old AAs. You want to be credited for actually doing something new and exciting? Implement some dual AAs for us. Some AAs that give a certain effect when in offensive form and another in healing form. And don't make them cost a million points either because if you think about it, we can't use them in normal mode and with the 5 minute delay on form change we wont be switching between sides of the effect all that quickly so perhaps a 5point AA would cost 6 or 7.<br><br>And as an afterthough. You gave us an epic with a pretty fair dmg/delay ratio. This is completely useless to us I mean honestly, if we are going to melee we are going to use a hammer of hours and that for the proc. In offensive, can we have some melee ability please? It's not like we can nuke and melee at the same time so it's not overpowering.<br><br>What I do NOT want to see is another wolf form please. That is outdated and annoying. You can't mount a mount on it and you can only cast it outdoors. That's really unfair when the best zones are indoors. I can't use these things on DoN missions, I can't use them in RS, heck I couldn't use them back in LDoN.<br><br>I know I said a lot and if ALL of it is implemented then perhaps we will be a bit overpowered but I post this in hopes that some or much of it will be implemented with modifications as sony sees fit (as long as this does not mean a 1 fight pet like clerics I'd rather not have one at all here). Obvious things that will be tossed out are pets, melee, and the dual AA BUT "especially" the dual AA is something I really think you should consider.	
		</td></tr>
