<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3520#M3520">56</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 763 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I am&nbsp;pretty happy with the proposed changes.&nbsp; Frankly, I see it as druids getting changes on the high end of the re-envisioning improvements scale, certainly a much greater improvement that "that other healing class".&nbsp; (I haven't read the cleric forum, but I suspect that they aren't honestly afraid of druids taking over the world, but they may&nbsp;have a&nbsp;right to be upset that in comparison they get... snare undead???&nbsp; Imagine if druids had been offered an improved fear animal...)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as it "not being enough" - bah humbug!&nbsp; We do&nbsp;NOT need to be improved so much that we can replace clerics (nor wizards).&nbsp; What we need is just this level of tweak so that when there isn't a cleric available, a group can pull in a druid and at least not stand around looking at the LFG tool.&nbsp; Will&nbsp;a group with a druid&nbsp;have as&nbsp;efficient healing&nbsp;as a group that did get a cleric?&nbsp; No.&nbsp; There might (gasp) be some downtime while we med.&nbsp; But that is better than spending another hour LFG while seeking&nbsp;a cleric.&nbsp; Heck, I get the occational group heal job now, in the right spot with the right group.&nbsp; Boost me 25% and that opens up more opportunities (sure not everywhere, but then that would obsolete clerics)/</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Take WoS for instance.&nbsp;&nbsp;As it is&nbsp;now, maybe I&nbsp;could heal&nbsp;with a top end tank and a good rounded group with crowd control and slows and good dps.&nbsp; But it wouldn't be pretty (better have a necro or paladin in the group for rez's).&nbsp; Give me 25% better healing and I could start turning the&nbsp;6&nbsp;characters in WoS LFG (LFG=0% efficiency)&nbsp;into a functional (but not optimal) group.&nbsp; And when a cleric is found?&nbsp; Boom - I'm DPS!&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And speaking of DPS.&nbsp; There are many (high end)&nbsp;encounters where druids are already valued for DPS or for spot healing and other utility roles (kiting).&nbsp; Boost druid DPS 25% and they will be that much more valuable in all encounters.&nbsp; I can see a tactic where all the druids start in heal mode and at a critical point switch to DPS for the final burn.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I like the shape-shift component&nbsp;that others have suggested to go along with the druid's mode.&nbsp; That's such a cool idea I have to suspect that the Dev's have also seen WoW and already had that in mind.&nbsp; Someone suggested wolf for offensive and treant for healing - I'd go for that.&nbsp; Just don't permanently root me while healing!?!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm a little confused by the folks that say we have 0% HoT.&nbsp; Is Nature's Recovery not dropping anymore?&nbsp; SotW?&nbsp; Replenishment?&nbsp;&nbsp;Druids don't have&nbsp;a cleric's HoT, but it isn't 0% either.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I noticed someone say that if this is what the changes are, they are retiring their druid.&nbsp; Um... so you are playing a druid now, but when you have the new ability to selectively boost your healing or dps practically on demand,&nbsp;or stay the same as you are now, you want us to believe you will quit?&nbsp; All I can say to that threat is: LOL!</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
