<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3521#M3521">57</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 763 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>People seem to be missing one important point about all of this.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you are in one mode, say "DPS" and the cleric drops (read dies) you can immediately hit the "HEAL MODE" button and become mini-cleric.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You just cannot switch back to DPS for 5 mins.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There has to be some trade-off for this level of flexability.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sure we will not be a Wizard in DPS mode but can Wizards switch to a Cleric on the fly?</DIV>
<DIV>Sure we will not be a Cleric in HEAL mode but can a Cleric switch to DPS on the fly?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you want to do both then stay in NORMAL mode the way we are now.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>When I raid I am asked to do one or the other. Considering that I currently HEAL and NUKE (depending on what is asked) in what is considered normal mode then why is a 25% boost not enough?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If SOE, instead of posting their current idea, was to come and say this:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We are going to boost all Druid heals by 25% people would be very very happy. We are getting both but I will once again say that I agree that a 50% penalty is far too much.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Make it 25% / 25% and I'm sold. Increase one and decrease another.... very logical and the fact that neither will put us anywhere near the ballpark of a Wizard or Cleric, and the 5 min delay switch, is enough balance IMHO.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes we do need other things to "fix" heals. Clerics do not cast "only" CH and a fast heal. They use many other types of spells.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Since Druids form of damage mitigation is Regen then double our regens and half the duration - IE Mini HoT</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>or</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Double or Damage Shields so that they truly do shorten battles (or make them stack with others!)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-Cass</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>P.S. Even I, an often staunch critic of SOE, do admit that Druids do have a level of versitility that Clerics and Wizards do not.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							March 2005<br><br>Druids are a unique challenge in that the class is divided evenly between you offensive druids who enjoy doing damage, and you defensive druids who prefer to play the role of healer. We want to support both play styles, but if we were to increase both halves of the druid equally the class would quickly become overpowered. Our plan is to introduce a new option where a druid can enter into a particular mode or stance where they become better at one part at the expense of the other. Our preferred solution for this is to add an innate ability for druids. The ability would get its own button similar to abilities such as backstab or track. You will be able to be in one of three states and can switch between them once every 5 minutes.<br
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
