			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=11140'>







<img src="http://i54.photobucket.com/albums/g112/sparkers70/5dragons.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3528#M3528">64</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 732 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>"If you are in one mode, say "DPS" and the cleric drops (read dies) you can immediately hit the "HEAL MODE" button and become mini-cleric." -Cassea-Eci</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That isn't how I understand this to work. When you enter a mode, you are locked into that mode for 5 minutes, and when that 5 minutes expires, so does whatever mode you had active. At that point you either remain in normal mode or choose between offense and defense.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So if you're in offense mode and the cleric dies, you may be waiting up to 4 minutes 59 seconds before you&nbsp;will be able to choose&nbsp;defense (Heal) mode... the amount of time you'll&nbsp;wait depends upon how long prior to the cleric's death you had&nbsp;activated offense mode. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In the situation you described,&nbsp;your heals are at&nbsp;half (&nbsp;<STRONG>- 50%</STRONG>) power because you are&nbsp;currently in DPS mode and waiting for X amount of time for that mode to wear off. If you're the only backup healer, your group is pretty much&nbsp;screwed. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Regards,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mahzz</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
