			<DIV>Nice compromise SoE - I cannot wait for the next few rounds of re-envisioning. I was pleasantly surprised by the general changes that everyone is going to get too.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I like the suggestion that a few people have posted re shape changing when you alter your 'stance' from Offensive to Normal to Healing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you do implement a shape change, don't use Wolf form for Offensive.... use Tiger form - that model is already a global model since Beastlord pets use it. A Tiger is far more aggressive than a Wolf and would look rather cool.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Brenlo's Coffee post dated 15th March hints at more changes for everyone to come. He said that some people got more of the pie this time and next time it will be someone elses turn, but everyone will still get a slice. It might be bigger it might be smaller <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>All in all any change to any class will make that class stronger and stronger means better groups and better raids and more dead foes. I just think everyone should get away from the 'size' envy that seems to inhabit the game world. As I have posted elsewhere if I've got a single shot bolt action rifle and my buddy has a machine gun when we are facing 10 enemies, I wouldn't think "waah he's got a bigger gun than me" - I would be thinking 'cool they haven't got a chance against us' - thats what we all should be thinking.</DIV>
