<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3530#M3530">66</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 720 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>1. What should the % increase be for the healing side? - Scirroco</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>I actually think that 25% is a good enough increase percentage wise. We really don't want to annoy the clerics too much and we aren't clerics. I do however think that the mana for our heals need to be brought into line with clerics. It doesn't even have to be the same, just closer to them 150% is to much of a difference. If we are to be 80% as good as clerics then our mana costs should be at very worst 120% not 150%</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>2. What additional healing tools (spells, skills) do we need? - Scirroco</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>It's been well documented that we still won't have the ability to heal like a cleric or anywhere near it. I can't begin to suggest how SoE are going to impliment this without stamping all over clerics but we have to have some way to heal groups and not just individuals. They could make a start to this by changing SotW. Making it heal more and fixing the reacst timer to something useable. It's a very fine line here and we have to not step over it.</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>3. What should the % increase be for the DPS side, and what spells does it apply to? - Scirroco</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
Again I think the actual percentage is fine as it is for healing. The thing here is the cast times and mana costs again. Bring them in to line with wizards and adjust them in accordance with the percentage of a wizard we are meant to be. It would be interesting if they removed the melee caps for us though <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<P>I'm starting love the proposals that SoE have made here but I'm very aware of the number of nerf bats that are being swung in other class boards. We have to be careful we don't ask for more than is fair. We have to show the rest of the game that we just want balance, we don't need to be totally uber. In my opinion it would ruin the game for all concerned if we were.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
