			>
			"it's that I like being able to get the goodies for myself (the new ones, plus the traditional stuff like foraging, porting, tracking, invising) and not getting the short end of the stick."<br><br>I'm sorry, but I really don't see where clerics get the short end of the stick. Take for example the case of a cleric who recently left my guild. He was taken in, MUCH under-geared, he was totally outfitted in a matter of days, he was given his epic 1.5 on a silver platter (heck the guild even showed him how to do it, because he didnt know anything about it).... And he quit playing after a couple months. THe cleric in question had no business being in our guild; he didnt have the experience, he didnt have a good attitude, he didnt have the gear. But because he was a cleric, even if a lowly one, he was taken in and pampered. WE do that *only* for clerics and rogues.<br><br>So try telling me again how clerics get the short end of the stick?<br><br>"From what I can see (and feel free to respond with your own opinions), the appeal of playing a druid is it's fun with all your special abilities and versatility, being useful alone or as part of a group, with the only real drawback being that you may not be the first choice for healer or dps/evacer."<br><br>You see wrong. It *should* be that way, but it's not. Solo is a much tougher proposition than it was. We are so far behind in healing that are only considered for the healing spot in a group as a last ditch alternative. We are not even top half in DPS anymore. I have a berzerker who clocks in at 600-700 DPS in my guild, and he says epic 2.0 will let this figure mount to 800-900. I have rogues in my guild that top 600 DPs. Wizards get 400-500 DPS, so do mages, etc. Druid DPS is not even close to that.<br><br>As far as evaccing... let's just say that you see in this much more use than it is.<br><br>"If every class could successfully solo with the efficiency of a druid"<br><br>Somehow you think druids are still kings of soloing, and you couldn't be more wrong. BLs, Necros, Bards, Wizards, all solo better. Paladins, SKs, Shamans, Mages, Chanters, Rangers, all solo about the same as druids.<br><br>I think you should revise your perception, because it's false.<br><br>Bluetiger	
