		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>An interesting idea.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Make the spells cost 20% less while in the pro-stance - and 100% more while in the opposite stance.</DIV>
<DIV>(note, 20% less cost is equal to a 25% bonus - and 100% higher cost is equal to a 50% penalty).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The idea has merit.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The most importent uncertainty though is the one debated above-</DIV>
<DIV>- do you "lock" yourself into a stance for 5 mins solid and then revert to normal before being able to pick a stance again </DIV>
<DIV>or</DIV>
<DIV>- do you pick a stance and then stay in it untill you pick another with the only restriction that you cannot change again within 5 mins</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I believe its the latter which is also by far the more powerfull. If its the former it has some negative implications that also balance the idea.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><p>Message Edited by Mikar on <span class=date_text>03-16-2005</span> <span class=time_text>07:32 AM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264> Mikar of the Nexus</A>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
