		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>"<EM>An outdated and broken aa fix and a spellline for lower level compared to what other classes get? You might call it envy i just call it unbalanced</EM>." -Pricilla Asagiri</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This phase of re-envisioning was primarily intended to look at <U>grouping desirability</U> and determine which classes are currently having difficulty finding groups. Clerics are the MOST desirable class for grouping, so logically&nbsp;they did not <EM>need</EM>&nbsp;to be fixed or helped in this phase.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Similarly,&nbsp;SOE did look at <U>soloing</U> capability&nbsp;and determined that clerics needed some help in that aspect of play.&nbsp;So,&nbsp;clerics were given a combat spell which allows them to proc a 550-point Damage Shield on themselves. (In fact, a&nbsp;damage&nbsp;shield&nbsp;that is *ten times*&nbsp;bigger than what a&nbsp;druid can cast.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>Having said all that, I'm&nbsp;curious&nbsp;.....</DIV>
<DIV align=left>Why are you on the DRUID board expressing your concerns for what the CLERIC class&nbsp;needs? </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>With all due respect, is it too much to ask that&nbsp;druids be allowed to have a discussion about druid issues on the druid message board, without constant interference from a cleric trying to make this a discussion about cleric issues?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Regards,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mahzz</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
